Biography

2022: Repeated as a USILA All-America Honorable Mention .... Earned Empire 8 All-Conference Second Team accolades ... Appeared in all 19 games with 10 starts in the midfield ... Had a career-high 51 points and tied his previous best with 31 assists ... Registered a point in every game ... Opened the season with five points (2g-3a) at Ithaca (2/26) ... Logged a season-high seven points (3g-4a) in a 20-14 win at Nazareth (4/2) ... Set a single-game career-high with four goals in a 31-3 win over Keuka (4/13) ... Dished out five assists as part of a six-point performance in the Empire 8 Championship against Nazareth (5/7).

2021: Named a USILA All-America Honorable Mention as a junior ... Voted to the Empire 8 All-Conference First Team ... Ranked fourth on the team in points (45) and led all Cardinals with a career-high-tying 31 assists ... Produced multiple points in 13 contests ... Logged a season-high seven points (2g-5a) in a season-opening win over Clarkson (3/7) ... Scored twice with four assists for six points against Nazareth (4/24) ... Had three assists and a season-high three ground balls in Fisher's NCAA Tournament win over SUNY Maritime (5/15).

2020: Appeared in all five games, starting two of them as a sophomore ... Tied for fifth on the team in points with seven (6g-1a) ... Netted his first career hat trick in the season-opener against Ithaca (2/22).

2019: Saw action in all 20 games as a freshman for the Cardinals ... Ranked third on the team with 24 assists and sixth with 39 points ... Recorded a point in all but one contest ... Began his collegiate career with six consecutive multi-point games, including a three-point effort (2g-1a) in his debut against Wooster (2/23) ... Handed out three assists against Brockport (3/13) and SUNY Geneseo (4/3).

High School: Earned varsity letters in lacrosse, football, and basketball ... Named Homer High School Athlete of the Year as a senior ... A two-time All-League First Team selection and team MVP in lacrosse ... Tabbed an All-State First-Team defensive back as a senior on the football team ... Won a sectional football title in the fall of his senior year and a lacrosse league championship in the spring.

Personal: Tucker is the son of Matt and Kathy ... Born January 23, 2000 ... Majoring in Physics and Computer Science.

No stats available for the current season.
